943	\subsection{$\AffineCoverMVSquare.X_4$ specialisation (iter-035)}
944	
945	With the iter-034 universal bridge $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ for terminal $T$ in scope, the natural specialisation lands the bridge on the $X_4$ corner of an $\AffineCoverMVSquare$. Iter-029's simp lemma $\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare\_toSquare\_X_4} : S.\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare}.\mathtt{toSquare}.X_4 = \top$ identifies the corner with the top open of the underlying scheme; Mathlib's $\mathtt{Preorder.isTerminalTop}$ supplies a witness $\mathtt{IsTerminal}\,(\top : \mathtt{TopologicalSpace.Opens}\,X.\mathtt{toTopCat})$. Composing the equation (transported via $\mathtt{Eq.symm}\,\blacktriangleright$) with the universal bridge gives the desired specialisation. The qualified $\mathtt{TopologicalSpace.Opens}$ form is required to sidestep the iter-029 sub-namespace shadowing trap.
946	
947	\begin{definition}\leanok
948	[$\AffineCoverMVSquare.X_4$ specialisation, abstract sheaf form, iter-035]
949	  \label{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv}
950	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.HModule'_X₄_linearEquiv}
951	  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_eq_HModule_linearEquiv, def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare, def:Scheme_HModule, def:Scheme_HModule_prime}
952	  Let $k$ be a field, $X : \Scheme$, $S : X.\AffineCoverMVSquare$, $F : \Sheaf\,(\mathtt{Opens.grothendieckTopology}\,X.\mathtt{toTopCat})\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$, $n \in \mathbb{N}$, and assume $\HasExt_u$ and $\HasExt_{u+1}$ for the same sheaf category. There is a $k$-linear isomorphism
953	  \[
954	    \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(S.\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare}.\mathtt{toSquare}.X_4)
955	    \;\equiv_{\Module k}\;
956	    \HModule\,k\,F\,n.
957	  \]
958	\end{definition}
959	
960	\begin{proof}
961	
962	\leanok
963	  Use $\mathtt{Eq.symm}\,\blacktriangleright$ on iter-029's $\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare\_toSquare\_X_4}$ to transport the witness $\mathtt{Preorder.isTerminalTop}\,(\mathtt{TopologicalSpace.Opens}\,X.\mathtt{toTopCat}) : \mathtt{IsTerminal}\,(\top : \mathtt{Opens}\,X.\mathtt{toTopCat})$ to an $\mathtt{IsTerminal}\,(S.\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare}.\mathtt{toSquare}.X_4)$. Apply Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_eq_HModule_linearEquiv} (iter-034) at this terminal corner. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-035 pass) confirms the one-liner typechecks end-to-end and produces kernel-only axioms.
964	\end{proof}
